Don't make me shoot you again.

260
00:17:08,093 --> 00:17:09,117
Again?

261
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:11,025
Is that the way we're gonna play it?

262
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:17,865
What are you doing
in my house, Agent Lloyd?

263
00:17:17,936 --> 00:17:20,837
Sitting, drinking, eating chocolate.

264
00:17:20,906 --> 00:17:23,841
- You have a warrant?
- FBI doesn't have jurisdiction here.

265
00:17:23,909 --> 00:17:25,536
I know, that's why I came down here.

266
00:17:25,611 --> 00:17:27,044
Oh, I don't think it is.

267
00:17:27,112 --> 00:17:30,343
The <i>Seven Seas Navigator</i>
docking here for a solid week.

268
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:33,351
They're having a nice promotion
for the maiden voyage,

269
00:17:33,419 --> 00:17:36,149
calling it the Diamond Cruise.

270
00:17:36,221 --> 00:17:39,247
A gem exhibit whose star attraction is

271
00:17:39,324 --> 00:17:41,451
the third Napoleon Diamond.

272
00:17:41,527 --> 00:17:43,927
Stop me when I get to the part
you don't know.

273
00:17:43,996 --> 00:17:46,260
It's the only one you two haven't stolen.

274
00:17:46,331 --> 00:17:47,355
Allegedly.

275
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:50,095
And it's gonna be right here
for a whole week... the last of the set...

276
00:17:50,169 --> 00:17:52,535
and I suspect you plan to purloin it.

277
00:17:52,604 --> 00:17:53,662
Well, I don't.

278
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:55,604
So finish your drink and get out.

279
00:17:55,674 --> 00:17:57,164
It's okay to be happy to see me.

280
00:17:57,242 --> 00:18:00,370
Just because you're English doesn't
mean you need to hide your emotions.

281
00:18:00,446 --> 00:18:02,471
I'm Irish.
We let people know how we feel.

282
00:18:02,548 --> 00:18:03,947
Now fuck off.

283
00:18:06,785 --> 00:18:09,549
And you can take any bugs you planted
along with you.

284
00:18:09,621 --> 00:18:11,179
I'm retired.

285
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:14,350
A retired guy wouldn't have anything
to worry about from those.

286
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:15,916
- Mind if I borrow this?
- Take it.

287
00:18:15,994 --> 00:18:17,586
You might learn something from it.

288
00:18:17,663 --> 00:18:19,426
But return it for me.
It's overdue.

289
00:18:19,498 --> 00:18:21,227
Give my love to Lola, will you?

290
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:34,336
How was the tennis lesson?

291
00:18:34,413 --> 00:18:37,314
Great. The teacher says I'm a natural.

292
00:18:37,382 --> 00:18:40,180
He says I've got the best backside
he's ever seen.

293
00:18:40,252 --> 00:18:41,310
That's <i>backhand.</i>

294
00:18:41,386 --> 00:18:42,512
Don't go in there.

295
00:18:42,588 --> 00:18:44,783
- Why?
- Let's talk.

296
00:18:45,924 --> 00:18:49,485
Okay, you're making me nervous,
and I don't get nervous.

297
00:18:51,196 --> 00:18:53,061
Agent Lloyd just left.

298
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,827
What's <i>he</i> doing here?

299
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,424
He came to show me this.

300
00:19:02,508 --> 00:19:04,874
Damn it, Max.

301
00:19:04,943 --> 00:19:06,433
Is this what we're here for?

302
00:19:06,512 --> 00:19:09,072
No. It's not.

303
00:19:11,517 --> 00:19:13,576
This is not retirement at all.

304
00:19:13,652 --> 00:19:16,086
This is the next setup, isn't it?

305
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:19,147
Babe, <i>you</i> chose
this island, remember?

306
00:19:21,293 --> 00:19:23,853
I hope you don't think
this is a gift from God.

307
00:19:23,929 --> 00:19:27,558
'Cause this is God messing with us.

308
00:19:32,304 --> 00:19:34,397
Oh, no. Max.

309
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:36,969
Did Stan do this?

310
00:19:37,042 --> 00:19:38,805
Sort of.

311
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:42,473
I figured he'd bug the place,
so I started checking.

312
00:19:42,548 --> 00:19:44,448
Did you find any?

313
00:19:44,516 --> 00:19:46,780
Only what he wanted me to find.

314
00:19:47,786 --> 00:19:49,481
There's another one here somewhere.

315
00:19:51,857 --> 00:19:53,484
Now, don't worry.
I already checked.

316
00:19:53,559 --> 00:19:54,753
There's nothing in there.

317
00:19:54,826 --> 00:19:56,350
That's the problem.

318
00:19:56,428 --> 00:19:58,055
There's nothing in here.

319
00:20:02,734 --> 00:20:04,258
What is it?
What's wrong?

320
00:20:04,336 --> 00:20:06,930
I hid the bullet in the camera.

321
00:20:07,005 --> 00:20:08,666
What bullet?

322
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:10,935
The one he shot you with.

323
00:20:11,009 --> 00:20:12,567
Oh, no.

324
00:20:13,779 --> 00:20:17,146
I kept it to remind me
of how close I came to losing you.

325
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:19,741
Lola, you know that bullet
puts me on the scene.

326
00:20:19,818 --> 00:20:22,548
I know, I know. I'm sorry.

327
00:20:22,621 --> 00:20:24,612
I'll get it back.

328
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:42,867
Good morning, Mr. Lloyd.
Your suite is ready.

329
00:20:42,941 --> 00:20:45,273
- Suite?
- Suite, sir.

330
00:20:45,344 --> 00:20:47,278
It's a larger room.

331
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:53,014
Atlantis reserves this bridge suite
for our more dignified guests.

332
00:20:56,221 --> 00:20:59,384
Breakfast is on the house, these are
vouchers for free tennis lessons,

333
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:03,360
complimentary skin exfoliant,
seaweed body wrap and facial scrub,

334
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:06,090
located in the spa on the club level.

335
00:21:06,164 --> 00:21:07,597
Also, please remember.

336
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:12,433
Shoes and shirt are required
in all public spaces at all times.

337
00:21:44,403 --> 00:21:45,631
State your business.

338
00:21:45,704 --> 00:21:48,730
You can't bribe me
with a seaweed body wrap, Max.

339
00:21:48,807 --> 00:21:50,468
This doesn't buy you one bit of space.

340
00:21:50,542 --> 00:21:52,635
I'm gonna be on you wherever you go.

341
00:21:52,711 --> 00:21:53,837
It's no bribe, Stanley.

342
00:21:53,912 --> 00:21:56,312
I just want you to see
that if you lead the kind of life I do,

343
00:21:56,381 --> 00:21:58,576
stealing is the last thing on your mind.

344
00:22:00,952 --> 00:22:01,941
Mr. Lloyd.

345
00:22:02,921 --> 00:22:04,616
Are you ready for your massage?

346
00:22:05,924 --> 00:22:07,755
I'll do your back.

347
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:09,760
I'll do your front.

348
00:22:10,929 --> 00:22:12,419
You son of a bitch.

349
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:24,070
- Lola?
- Yeah.

350
00:22:25,577 --> 00:22:28,603
- He hid it in a black jewelry box.
- Good job.

351
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,977
Thank you.

352
00:22:30,048 --> 00:22:31,948
Talented masseuse.

353
00:22:32,784 --> 00:22:33,944
You get rid of it this time.

354
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,509
I will.

355
00:22:36,355 --> 00:22:38,323
Good evening.
May I take your order?

356
00:22:40,292 --> 00:22:42,317
No, thank you.
I just lost my appetite.

357
00:22:42,394 --> 00:22:43,622
Just as well.

358
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:46,493
I don't take orders from criminals,
I arrest them.

359
00:22:46,565 --> 00:22:48,157
Or fall asleep trying.

360
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,395
So you're admitting you were there.

361
00:22:50,469 --> 00:22:53,438
No. I read about it in the papers,
just like everyone else.

362
00:22:53,505 --> 00:22:55,496
You're famous.

363
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:57,865
I'm a punchline.

364
00:22:58,477 --> 00:23:02,607
But like my grandma used to say,
he who laughs last laughs loudest.

365
00:23:02,681 --> 00:23:04,444
By the way,
return that movie, would you?

366
00:23:04,516 --> 00:23:06,108
The store called.

367
00:23:06,184 --> 00:23:07,913
I haven't finished it yet.

368
00:23:07,986 --> 00:23:11,114
They catch the thief,
but it's not who you think it is.

369
00:23:11,189 --> 00:23:13,157
I don't like those twist endings.

370
00:23:13,225 --> 00:23:14,658
Well, we don't like you.

371
00:23:14,726 --> 00:23:16,455
Aw w.

372
00:23:16,528 --> 00:23:17,517
Lola.

373
00:23:19,131 --> 00:23:20,655
They're playing your song.

374
00:23:20,732 --> 00:23:23,724
Why don't you take Stanley
for a dance?

375
00:23:23,802 --> 00:23:25,360
He's feeling lonely.

376
00:23:25,437 --> 00:23:28,133
And I am feeling charitable.

377
00:23:28,874 --> 00:23:30,341
Let's go, Stan.

378
00:23:30,509 --> 00:23:31,635
Really?

379
00:23:33,178 --> 00:23:35,237
I'll try to have her back by dawn.

380
00:23:49,828 --> 00:23:51,022
Constable...

381
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:54,330
Can I help you?

382
00:23:54,399 --> 00:23:56,196
I wanna talk to Mooré.

383
00:23:56,268 --> 00:23:57,599
Get out of the way.

384
00:23:57,669 --> 00:24:00,502
Monsieur Mooré is currently socializing.

385
00:24:00,572 --> 00:24:03,507
Interrupting a man's leisure
is harassment.

386
00:24:03,575 --> 00:24:05,941
That's not harassment.

387
00:24:07,312 --> 00:24:08,609
You feel that?

388
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,944
- Ooh.
- That's harassment.

389
00:24:11,016 --> 00:24:15,146
And you tell your boss
this is just the beginning.

390
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:18,553
I have two hands,
and I can't be bought.

391
00:24:18,623 --> 00:24:19,612
Ooh.

392
00:24:23,562 --> 00:24:26,326
Excuse me, constable.
May I have a word with you?

393
00:24:35,106 --> 00:24:38,735
<i>Audrey, where you get that sugar?</i>

394
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:40,937
Listen, Stan,
I know what you're doing.

395
00:24:41,012 --> 00:24:45,073
But if you drag Max into your game,
he will not lose.

396
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:47,175
Eventually, they all lose.

397
00:24:47,252 --> 00:24:48,844
Not my Max.

398
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:51,354
Do yourself a favor...
leave us alone.

399
00:24:51,423 --> 00:24:55,416
We're just a couple of retirees
trying to enjoy the island life.

400
00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:58,986
All the same, I'll stick around,
see what develops.

401
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:01,660
Excuse me.

402
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:03,394
In a second, honey.
You'll get your chance.

403
00:25:03,468 --> 00:25:06,266
Damn, I got the stink on me tonight.

404
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:08,067
Step off the dance floor, sir.

405
00:25:08,874 --> 00:25:10,341
Hey!

406
00:25:10,408 --> 00:25:12,137
- Have fun, Stan.
- Hey. Lola!

407
00:25:12,210 --> 00:25:14,838
Police.
Raise your hands, sir.

408
00:25:15,847 --> 00:25:18,611
I'm law.
Federal B.I.?

409
00:25:25,290 --> 00:25:29,488
It is illegal on this island to carry
a concealed weapon without a permit.

410
00:25:29,561 --> 00:25:31,188
I'm working a suspect.

411
00:25:34,266 --> 00:25:36,962
Are you not supposed to inform
local authorities when you arrive,

412
00:25:37,035 --> 00:25:39,526
Agent Stanley P. Lloyd?

413
00:25:42,841 --> 00:25:45,002
- You know him?
- He's my suspect.

414
00:25:45,076 --> 00:25:48,307
Well, we're still gonna have to
take this to the station and register it.

415
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:49,677
You're letting the criminal go.

416
00:25:49,748 --> 00:25:50,942
This is crazy.

417
00:25:51,016 --> 00:25:52,574
You think this is crazy?

418
00:25:52,651 --> 00:25:55,449
Your dancing, <i>that</i> was crazy.

419
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:57,078
This way, Agent Lloyd.

420
00:25:57,155 --> 00:25:59,123
Welcome to paradise.

421
00:26:04,095 --> 00:26:05,357
Okay.

422
00:26:05,430 --> 00:26:08,365
- The watermarks and holograms match.
- Oh.

423
00:26:08,433 --> 00:26:10,560
But I still have to register the gun.

424
00:26:16,274 --> 00:26:17,866
You have a nice smile.

425
00:26:17,943 --> 00:26:19,774
I haven't smiled at you.

426
00:26:19,844 --> 00:26:21,471
You will.

427
00:26:23,982 --> 00:26:26,450
That's just the way I feel about it,
and they have to deal with it.

428
00:26:26,518 --> 00:26:27,542
Yes, sir.

429
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:29,652
Ah, Sophie.

430
00:26:29,721 --> 00:26:31,552
I need to speak to you.

431
00:26:31,623 --> 00:26:34,217
I'm getting complaints
about you bothering Henri Mooré.

432
00:26:34,292 --> 00:26:36,283
Just doing my job, Zacharias.

433
00:26:36,361 --> 00:26:38,420
The man is practically
the unofficial mayor of the island.

434
00:26:38,496 --> 00:26:40,123
In one year, he's made
everyone here like him,

435
00:26:40,198 --> 00:26:42,063
something you haven't been
able to do in a lifetime.

436
00:26:42,133 --> 00:26:44,897
I guess we can't all be
the kiss-ass politician you are.

437
00:26:45,670 --> 00:26:48,571
I want you to stay behind tonight
so we can discuss your attitude.

438
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,301
You knew about my attitude
the day we got married

439
00:26:50,375 --> 00:26:51,865
and knew about it
the day we got divorced.

440
00:26:51,943 --> 00:26:54,776
You're not gonna learn
any more about it tonight.

441
00:26:54,846 --> 00:26:58,782
Besides, I have plans
with Special Agent Lloyd of the FBI.

442
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:00,875
He's just arrived on the island.

443
00:27:01,553 --> 00:27:02,747
Is that so?

444
00:27:03,588 --> 00:27:04,646
Shall we?

445
00:27:04,723 --> 00:27:06,384
We shall.

446
00:27:11,162 --> 00:27:12,857
She's feisty.

447
00:27:17,969 --> 00:27:21,427
Mmm. Isn't it beautiful?

448
00:27:22,841 --> 00:27:24,001
Yeah.

449
00:27:26,177 --> 00:27:27,906
Is it enough?

450
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:29,875
Of course it is.

451
00:27:42,761 --> 00:27:46,128
Some people say the only way
to rid yourself of temptation

452
00:27:46,197 --> 00:27:48,290
is to yield to it.

453
00:27:50,468 --> 00:27:52,197
I don't know about that.

454
00:27:54,272 --> 00:27:59,266
I say turn your back on temptation...

455
00:28:00,078 --> 00:28:05,311
...or substitute something
more tempting.

456
00:28:19,597 --> 00:28:21,929
See how easy that was?

457
00:28:31,142 --> 00:28:33,576
What's the shortest amount of time
you've ever known a guy

458
00:28:33,645 --> 00:28:37,172
before you kissed him?

459
00:28:37,782 --> 00:28:40,580
I see what you're thinking,
and you can forget it.

460
00:28:40,652 --> 00:28:44,554
Guys come down to this island looking
for a slice of paradise with a local girl,

461
00:28:44,622 --> 00:28:46,954
and they will say anything to get it.

462
00:28:48,026 --> 00:28:50,654
I resent being lumped in with all guys,

463
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:53,960
though, admittedly,
I would say anything right now.

464
00:28:54,032 --> 00:28:56,330
How long have you been chasing Max?

465
00:28:58,336 --> 00:29:02,295
Seven years... ever since the first
Napoleon Diamond went missing.

466
00:29:02,373 --> 00:29:05,433
I got to the scene,
took a few shots at the getaway car.

467
00:29:05,510 --> 00:29:10,174
Next day, bottle of champagne arrives
at FBI Headquarters for me,

468
00:29:10,248 --> 00:29:15,049
with a note says,
"Aim for the tires next time."

469
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:16,781
He was baiting you.

470
00:29:16,855 --> 00:29:19,790
- Hmm.
- Is there a money trail?

471
00:29:19,858 --> 00:29:22,850
Everything's plain...
taxes, bank accounts.

472
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:26,158
He doesn't buy
expensive paintings, yachts, nothing.

473
00:29:26,231 --> 00:29:31,294
I think it's more about the challenge
and the alibi... that's his work of art.

474
00:29:31,369 --> 00:29:33,200
Sounds like you admire him.

475
00:29:34,172 --> 00:29:37,767
Would I like to live one day
in his velvety slippers?

476
00:29:37,842 --> 00:29:39,275
Maybe.

477
00:29:39,344 --> 00:29:41,209
But I don't admire him.

478
00:29:41,279 --> 00:29:43,304
He's beat me too many times for that.

479
00:29:43,381 --> 00:29:45,576
Maybe you need the female touch.

480
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:49,143
That's exactly what I need.

481
00:29:49,220 --> 00:29:52,712
Listen, I want a big arrest,
you need local help.

482
00:29:52,791 --> 00:29:55,157
I'll extend the FBI courtesy on this one.

483
00:29:55,226 --> 00:29:57,592
As long as I'm riding shotgun.

484
00:30:05,336 --> 00:30:06,530
What's going on?

485
00:30:06,604 --> 00:30:08,697
I'm expanding the deck.

486
00:30:08,773 --> 00:30:10,434
You're trying to stay busy.

487
00:30:10,508 --> 00:30:13,671
Look, on this deck,
we are going to sit here

488
00:30:13,745 --> 00:30:16,771
and watch sunsets until we get old.

489
00:30:17,515 --> 00:30:19,107
Can't wait.

490
00:30:19,184 --> 00:30:20,776
Where are you going?

491
00:30:20,852 --> 00:30:22,376
You said I need a hobby.

492
00:30:22,453 --> 00:30:24,444
I guess I'll go find one.

493
00:30:24,522 --> 00:30:25,546
Really?

494
00:30:25,623 --> 00:30:27,750
I'll call you later.

495
00:30:58,223 --> 00:30:59,349
He's here.

496
00:31:06,931 --> 00:31:09,092
The centerpiece of our exhibit.

497
00:31:09,167 --> 00:31:12,625
Napoleon had three priceless diamonds
set into the hilt of his sword.

498
00:31:12,704 --> 00:31:15,798
After his defeat, they were pried out
and dispersed around the globe.

499
00:31:15,874 --> 00:31:19,833
This is one of the rare occasions the last
remaining diamond is on public display.

500
00:31:19,911 --> 00:31:22,505
And next, we have
some rare Egyptian gems.

501
00:31:51,209 --> 00:31:52,836
Cute little rock.

502
00:31:52,911 --> 00:31:54,640
I'm just here to look.

503
00:31:54,712 --> 00:31:55,838
Just as well.

504
00:31:55,914 --> 00:31:59,213
With six cameras...
four stationary, two revolving,

505
00:31:59,284 --> 00:32:01,047
a dozen I.R. Motion sensors...

506
00:32:01,119 --> 00:32:03,781
Sixteen.
You missed the ones at ankle level.

507
00:32:03,855 --> 00:32:06,323
Plus your standard
24-hour rotating guards.

508
00:32:06,391 --> 00:32:08,882
Unbreakable polycarbonate display,

509
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:11,758
controlled by an uncopyable
magnetic key card.

510
00:32:13,665 --> 00:32:17,726
I just realized...
you could never get it anyway.

511
00:32:21,205 --> 00:32:22,433
You're right.

512
00:32:23,608 --> 00:32:25,508
When you're right, you're right.

513
00:32:26,244 --> 00:32:27,575
It's impossible.

514
00:33:13,992 --> 00:33:15,391
Give me a ride.

515
00:33:15,460 --> 00:33:16,620
I don't think so.

516
00:33:16,694 --> 00:33:18,889
Maybe you should think again.

517
