01:08:45,955 --> 01:08:48,253
Stan's hurt.
He's in pain.

1021
01:08:48,324 --> 01:08:50,087
He's like a wounded dog.

1022
01:08:50,159 --> 01:08:52,889
He needs you, Lola.
You're his better half.

1023
01:08:52,962 --> 01:08:54,259
Just give him one more chance.

1024
01:08:54,330 --> 01:08:56,264
He's a good guy, Sophie.

1025
01:08:56,332 --> 01:08:59,733
I'm sure he's a liar,
but that comes with the job.

1026
01:09:00,636 --> 01:09:03,537
I don't know.
This is all a bit strange.

1027
01:09:03,606 --> 01:09:05,335
What do you think, Lola?

1028
01:09:05,407 --> 01:09:07,898
- I don't buy a word of it.
- I'm with you.

1029
01:09:07,977 --> 01:09:09,308
- No, no, no.
- Hey, hey, hey.

1030
01:09:09,378 --> 01:09:10,709
- Listen, hear us out.
- Come on, one second.

1031
01:09:10,779 --> 01:09:11,768
Look...

1032
01:09:13,816 --> 01:09:16,478
Tonight the lies stop.

1033
01:09:16,552 --> 01:09:18,042
He's serious. It's over.

1034
01:09:18,120 --> 01:09:20,816
He's not chasin' it,
and I'm not chasin' him.

1035
01:09:20,890 --> 01:09:24,417
I'm sorry, but I won't believe you
until that ship is gone.

1036
01:09:24,493 --> 01:09:26,552
And we still got a few hours
before she sails.

1037
01:09:26,629 --> 01:09:28,824
Look, I can't make
that ship disappear tonight,

1038
01:09:28,898 --> 01:09:30,229
but I can make us disappear.

1039
01:09:30,299 --> 01:09:33,700
- What are you talking about?
- I found a hobby.

1040
01:09:35,638 --> 01:09:37,401
Wait a minute.
You didn't tell me about this.

1041
01:09:37,473 --> 01:09:39,338
When we come up for air,

1042
01:09:39,408 --> 01:09:43,310
that ship will be headed to Paris
and the diamond will be gone forever.

1043
01:10:05,768 --> 01:10:07,633
So, where you taking us?

1044
01:10:07,703 --> 01:10:09,933
We're headed to a hidden reef
where there's rumored to be

1045
01:10:10,005 --> 01:10:12,496
100 million in gold
somewhere among the wreckage.

1046
01:10:13,342 --> 01:10:14,673
You're kidding.

1047
01:10:17,947 --> 01:10:18,971
Wow!

1048
01:10:19,048 --> 01:10:20,811
Look at this.

1049
01:10:20,883 --> 01:10:23,943
Yeah, these ships have
been down here since the '40s,

1050
01:10:24,019 --> 01:10:26,385
but nobody's ever
found any gold.

1051
01:10:26,455 --> 01:10:29,390
Well, maybe with the help
of the FBI we'll get lucky.

1052
01:10:30,459 --> 01:10:32,290
My money's on Max.

1053
01:10:32,361 --> 01:10:36,422
100 million four ways...
that's 25 million a piece if we split it.

1054
01:10:40,736 --> 01:10:43,068
Have any idea where to start?

1055
01:10:43,138 --> 01:10:46,869
It could be anywhere down here.
Let's split up, look around.

1056
01:10:48,577 --> 01:10:52,911
You guys sure this is safe?
I'm allergic to shellfish.

1057
01:10:52,982 --> 01:10:56,679
You've got nothing to worry about.
I've seen how you handle sharks.

1058
01:11:24,980 --> 01:11:28,575
When we get back,
I'm buying everyone umbrella drinks.

1059
01:11:35,457 --> 01:11:39,325
Hey, little guy,
have you seen any gold down here?

1060
01:11:46,969 --> 01:11:50,700
Hey, Max, I'm counting on you
to make me a rich man.

1061
01:12:32,047 --> 01:12:34,743
Lola, hypothetically speaking,

1062
01:12:34,817 --> 01:12:37,684
what's it like to hold
25 million in your hands?

1063
01:12:38,487 --> 01:12:40,921
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

1064
01:12:41,724 --> 01:12:42,713
Right.

1065
01:12:57,506 --> 01:13:00,373
- Good night, old-timer.
- Eat shit.

1066
01:13:39,782 --> 01:13:41,545
What the hell is that?

1067
01:13:44,586 --> 01:13:47,248
There is an intruder
in Storage Facility B.

1068
01:13:47,322 --> 01:13:49,449
- <i>Attempted break-in in progress.</i>
- Son of a bitch!

1069
01:13:49,525 --> 01:13:52,016
<i>All security</i>
<i>to Storage Facility B.</i>

1070
01:15:15,577 --> 01:15:16,635
<i>Hey, Max.</i>

1071
01:15:19,515 --> 01:15:20,504
What's up?

1072
01:15:20,582 --> 01:15:22,516
Where are you?

1073
01:15:22,584 --> 01:15:25,075
Oh, I'm somewhere inside the ship.

1074
01:15:25,153 --> 01:15:28,452
Oh, yeah, me too.
Thanks, that helps a lot.

1075
01:15:28,524 --> 01:15:31,891
Max, did you say
you were <i>inside</i> the ship?

1076
01:15:32,594 --> 01:15:35,085
Yeah, it's amazing.

1077
01:15:35,163 --> 01:15:38,360
Hmm. Really?
What do you see?

1078
01:15:38,433 --> 01:15:42,301
<i>It's pretty dark.</i>
<i>I think I'm in the captain's quarters.</i>

1079
01:15:42,371 --> 01:15:44,032
That's interesting.

1080
01:15:49,645 --> 01:15:53,706
Max, suddenly I don't feel like
having an umbrella drink.

1081
01:16:05,894 --> 01:16:08,556
I'm beginning to think we're gonna
go home empty-handed.

1082
01:16:08,630 --> 01:16:11,155
Where are you, Max?
I'm gonna come hunt with you a while.

1083
01:16:11,233 --> 01:16:13,497
I'm coming to you.

1084
01:16:14,202 --> 01:16:17,137
How you see me?
I cut the red wire.

1085
01:16:17,205 --> 01:16:21,369
Ah, nice work, genius.
You cut the heating to the Jacuzzi.

1086
01:16:23,679 --> 01:16:26,239
<i>Max, you at the stern?</i>

1087
01:16:28,450 --> 01:16:29,747
<i>Max?</i>

1088
01:16:33,121 --> 01:16:35,783
<i>Stan Lloyd to Max Burdett.</i>
<i>Come in.</i>

1089
01:16:39,628 --> 01:16:42,222
Who'd he think he was,
the Invisible Man?

1090
01:16:45,200 --> 01:16:46,531
Dear God.

1091
01:16:46,602 --> 01:16:48,729
Shit.

1092
01:16:48,804 --> 01:16:50,931
It was a diversion.
Get back to the diamond!

1093
01:16:52,874 --> 01:16:54,899
<i>Max, where are you?</i>

1094
01:17:02,084 --> 01:17:03,574
<i>Will you answer me?</i>

1095
01:17:03,652 --> 01:17:04,949
<i>Hello!</i>

1096
01:17:05,020 --> 01:17:06,317
There!

1097
01:17:13,862 --> 01:17:16,387
He's in the vents!
He got the diamond!

1098
01:17:16,465 --> 01:17:18,126
Max, what was that?

1099
01:17:18,200 --> 01:17:19,895
<i>Max!</i>

1100
01:17:19,968 --> 01:17:21,799
I think he left his radio.

1101
01:17:21,870 --> 01:17:24,270
I thought I heard
something else.

1102
01:17:24,873 --> 01:17:27,273
<i>Where'd you go?</i>
<i>Is something wrong?</i>

1103
01:17:43,525 --> 01:17:45,493
Nice costume.

1104
01:17:46,762 --> 01:17:48,354
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

1105
01:17:49,998 --> 01:17:52,523
<i>Party all the time,</i>
<i>party all the time</i>

1106
01:17:52,601 --> 01:17:55,069
<i>Party all the time</i>

1107
01:17:55,137 --> 01:17:58,231
<i>My girl wants</i>
<i>to party all the time...</i>

1108
01:17:58,306 --> 01:18:00,831
Go back to your cabin, please.

1109
01:18:02,144 --> 01:18:04,237
Aha, there you are!

1110
01:18:04,312 --> 01:18:05,574
Hey, Max, come on.

1111
01:18:05,647 --> 01:18:07,842
Last night we were spooning.
Now you're running away?

1112
01:18:09,117 --> 01:18:10,641
<i>Come on!</i>

1113
01:18:11,219 --> 01:18:13,517
Yoo-hoo, Max.

1114
01:18:30,272 --> 01:18:33,298
Oh, I get it.
A little hide-and-seek.

1115
01:18:42,551 --> 01:18:45,645
Like I told you on the boat,
I caught 'em all.

1116
01:18:53,061 --> 01:18:55,825
You're good,
but you're not that good.

1117
01:19:01,369 --> 01:19:05,362
You know what they say...
the FBI always gets their man.

1118
01:19:08,777 --> 01:19:10,301
Max!

1119
01:19:10,378 --> 01:19:12,107
I'm having an air problem!

1120
01:19:13,148 --> 01:19:14,979
Stan, are you okay?

1121
01:19:15,050 --> 01:19:17,917
I can't breathe! Help!

1122
01:19:19,921 --> 01:19:21,354
Where are you, Stan?

1123
01:19:24,259 --> 01:19:25,886
I'm coming, Stan.

1124
01:19:25,961 --> 01:19:28,759
It's okay, Stan.
I'm right here.

1125
01:19:28,830 --> 01:19:30,092
Take off your mask.

1126
01:19:30,966 --> 01:19:32,092
I got him, honey.

1127
01:19:32,167 --> 01:19:33,794
I'm right here.

1128
01:19:34,803 --> 01:19:36,703
You're okay, Stan.

1129
01:19:38,974 --> 01:19:41,033
Nothing to worry about, partner.

1130
01:19:46,648 --> 01:19:49,481
I saw my life flash
before my eyes.

1131
01:19:49,551 --> 01:19:51,917
Leave it to me to get
the faulty regulator.

1132
01:19:51,987 --> 01:19:54,455
You know,
I never dove before.

1133
01:19:55,023 --> 01:19:58,186
- I would like to propose a toast.
- What are we celebrating?

1134
01:19:59,027 --> 01:20:00,051
Retirement.

1135
01:20:01,630 --> 01:20:03,325
- I'll drink to that.
- Good.

1136
01:20:07,469 --> 01:20:08,527
Hello.

1137
01:20:10,238 --> 01:20:11,535
What?

1138
01:20:11,606 --> 01:20:12,937
How?

1139
01:20:13,775 --> 01:20:15,902
- What's wrong?
- The diamond's been stolen.

1140
01:20:15,977 --> 01:20:18,912
- What?
- Half an hour ago.

1141
01:20:22,150 --> 01:20:23,276
You set us up.

1142
01:20:23,351 --> 01:20:24,545
Come on.

1143
01:20:24,619 --> 01:20:26,086
This whole thing.

1144
01:20:27,155 --> 01:20:30,056
You got your perfect alibi... me.

1145
01:20:30,125 --> 01:20:31,888
Hey.

1146
01:20:31,960 --> 01:20:33,723
Get your hands up.

1147
01:20:33,795 --> 01:20:35,660
Are you serious?

1148
01:20:35,730 --> 01:20:37,391
No wonder you just retired.

1149
01:20:37,465 --> 01:20:40,662
You don't have
anything left to steal.

1150
01:20:40,735 --> 01:20:42,430
I've got to get to the ship.

1151
01:20:43,238 --> 01:20:44,500
You couldn't resist, could you?

1152
01:20:44,573 --> 01:20:46,632
You had to screw me
one last time.

1153
01:20:46,708 --> 01:20:49,336
You had to make an ass
out of me!

1154
01:20:56,852 --> 01:20:59,616
Hey, Lola.
Lola, wait.

1155
01:21:08,763 --> 01:21:09,821
Hey.

1156
01:21:14,336 --> 01:21:16,429
You really did save me down there.

1157
01:21:24,012 --> 01:21:27,641
I'm sorry I kept you in the dark.
I was only trying to protect you.

1158
01:21:27,716 --> 01:21:28,876
How generous of you.

1159
01:21:28,950 --> 01:21:31,441
You were right, you know.
I couldn't do it without you.

1160
01:21:31,519 --> 01:21:35,114
You gotta admit, though,
the look on Stan's face was sheer poetry.

1161
01:21:35,190 --> 01:21:36,885
Shut up, Max.

1162
01:21:36,958 --> 01:21:38,016
Hey.

1163
01:21:40,228 --> 01:21:41,593
Lola, please.

1164
01:21:42,564 --> 01:21:45,431
Max, I helped you
because I love you.

1165
01:21:45,500 --> 01:21:47,229
But now I'm leaving you.

1166
01:21:54,175 --> 01:21:57,144
Lola, I thought you'd
appreciate how I did it,

1167
01:21:57,212 --> 01:22:00,306
you of all people.
Hey, hey.

1168
01:22:02,584 --> 01:22:05,712
I do.
It was a smart plan, Max.

1169
01:22:05,787 --> 01:22:08,051
You're a great thief.

1170
01:22:08,890 --> 01:22:10,289
But I want a great man.

1171
01:22:17,198 --> 01:22:18,756
Lola.

1172
01:22:21,436 --> 01:22:22,801
Move inside.

1173
01:22:25,373 --> 01:22:28,001
What, you thought this was over?
Turn around!

1174
01:22:30,812 --> 01:22:33,212
I tried to deal with you
from an elevated place, man,

1175
01:22:33,281 --> 01:22:35,749
appeal to your intellect,
spit poetry and shit at you.

1176
01:22:35,817 --> 01:22:38,377
But no, man, you had to bring me
down to the gutter.

1177
01:22:38,453 --> 01:22:39,613
Where is the diamond?

1178
01:22:39,688 --> 01:22:42,350
- She's got nothing to do with this.
- Oh, she does now.

1179
01:22:42,424 --> 01:22:44,688
You kill my dog,
I'm gonna slay your cat.

1180
01:22:44,759 --> 01:22:46,192
Don't get...

1181
01:22:54,035 --> 01:22:55,263
Aah!

1182
01:22:56,104 --> 01:22:58,572
Nice throw, bitch!

1183
01:22:58,640 --> 01:23:00,267
No!

1184
01:23:06,081 --> 01:23:07,605
Where'd you come from?

1185
01:23:47,022 --> 01:23:49,889
He asked me to help him steal it
a week ago. I turned him down.

1186
01:23:49,958 --> 01:23:51,448
He must have stolen it himself,

1187
01:23:51,526 --> 01:23:54,461
then he came back here
to make sure there were no loose ends.

1188
01:23:54,529 --> 01:23:57,020
So why didn't you come to me,
tell me what they were planning?

1189
01:23:57,098 --> 01:23:58,656
He said he'd kill us.

1190
01:23:58,733 --> 01:24:00,428
You wouldn't have believed him anyway.

1191
01:24:00,502 --> 01:24:02,595
You thought Mooré was
the Second Coming for this island.

1192
01:24:02,670 --> 01:24:04,661
Don't tell me
what I think, woman.

1193
01:24:05,740 --> 01:24:08,106
- Where's the diamond?
- I have no idea.

1194
01:24:08,176 --> 01:24:11,339
- They were trying to frame us.
- Are we finished here?

1195
01:24:15,250 --> 01:24:17,912
You know, I don't believe a word
of what you're saying.

1196
01:24:18,553 --> 01:24:19,781
I know.

1197
01:24:37,939 --> 01:24:39,372
Don't leave.

1198
01:24:42,577 --> 01:24:44,169
Good luck, Max.

1199
01:26:08,630 --> 01:26:09,892
Lola, wait.

1200
01:26:10,331 --> 01:26:11,992
Hear me out.

1201
01:26:12,066 --> 01:26:15,092
It's not gonna work, Max.
Not this time.

1202
01:26:15,170 --> 01:26:18,662
I know it's too late,
but I finally wrote them. See?

1203
01:26:19,340 --> 01:26:20,568
Lots of words.

1204
01:26:20,642 --> 01:26:23,270
But I don't need to read them
because I know it by heart.

1205
01:26:24,145 --> 01:26:28,013
I've spent my whole life chasing things
which I thought were valuable,

1206
01:26:28,082 --> 01:26:31,483
when the only thing I really cared for
was right in front of me all along.

1207
01:26:33,821 --> 01:26:35,686
You are my heart, Lola.

1208
01:26:36,758 --> 01:26:39,488
From this moment on,
you are my only jewel.

1209
01:26:40,295 --> 01:26:43,162
I want a life
filled with sunsets.

1210
01:26:43,231 --> 01:26:46,860
And I never wanna watch
one of them without you, not ever.

1211
01:26:53,408 --> 01:26:55,672
The first diamond I've ever bought.

1212
01:26:58,980 --> 01:27:02,245
I love you, Lola Cirillo.

1213
01:27:04,052 --> 01:27:05,485
Marry me.

1214
01:27:15,997 --> 01:27:18,431
- On one condition.
- Anything.

1215
01:27:19,000 --> 01:27:20,524
I want the receipt.

1216
01:27:30,812 --> 01:27:31,801
Here you go, Luc.

1217
01:27:31,879 --> 01:27:33,437
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1218
01:27:33,514 --> 01:27:36,915
Jack on the rocks, with an umbrella.
What the hell, I'm celebrating.

1219
01:27:37,418 --> 01:27:40,285
Forget the Jack on the rocks,
let's have remoras all around.

1220
01:27:40,355 --> 01:27:41,845
Remoras all around.

1221
01:27:41,923 --> 01:27:44,323
Stanley, what the hell
are you doing here?

1222
01:27:44,392 --> 01:27:46,986
Well, I thought I'd stick around.

1223
01:27:48,663 --> 01:27:50,824
Oh, yeah, look familiar?

1224
01:27:50,898 --> 01:27:53,230
Treated myself,
maxed out the credit card.

1225
01:27:53,301 --> 01:27:54,859
But it suits me,
don't you think?

1226
01:27:54,936 --> 01:27:57,769
Well, it must take a bite
out of a government salary.

1227
01:27:57,839 --> 01:27:59,864
Ah, I can afford it all right.

1228
01:28:00,842 --> 01:28:03,777
Come on, let's sip
our remoras and talk, shall we?

1229
01:28:21,896 --> 01:28:23,887
I thought you said
these things have a kick.

1230
01:28:26,968 --> 01:28:28,629
Luc, what's in this?

1231
01:28:28,703 --> 01:28:32,002
Orange juice, mango juice,
grenadine, and coconut milk.

1232
01:28:33,675 --> 01:28:34,664
No liquor?

1233
01:28:38,379 --> 01:28:39,471
<i>Nada.</i>

1234
01:28:42,183 --> 01:28:44,549
I love these remoras!

1235
01:28:44,619 --> 01:28:46,678
Bartender, give me another!

1236
01:28:52,794 --> 01:28:55,228
You tell anyone I tucked him in,
I'll kill you.

1237
01:28:56,331 --> 01:28:59,129
- Sure thing, Mr. Burdett.
- Call me Max.

1238
01:28:59,200 --> 01:29:00,690
- Max.
- Okay.

1239
01:29:08,676 --> 01:29:12,043
You know,
I really like that cove.

1240
01:29:20,021 --> 01:29:22,888
Are you okay?
'Cause you don't look too good.

1241
01:29:27,061 --> 01:29:31,555
As an underwater enthusiast, you should
know what a remora really is, Max.

1242
01:29:31,632 --> 01:29:34,658
A remora is
kind of a stowaway,

1243
01:29:34,736 --> 01:29:39,264
a suckerfish that sticks
to the shark's body and feeds off it.

1244
01:29:39,340 --> 01:29:41,035
The shark does all the work,

1245
01:29:41,109 --> 01:29:44,306
but the remora gets the spoils.

1246
01:29:56,657 --> 01:29:57,988
You did it, Stan.

1247
01:30:00,795 --> 01:30:02,262
Right from the start.

1248
01:30:03,264 --> 01:30:05,664
It's the only one
you two haven't stolen.

1249
01:30:06,768 --> 01:30:08,167
You set me up.

1250
01:30:08,236 --> 01:30:11,069
I revel in it.
I revel in it!

1251
01:30:16,177 --> 01:30:20,079
Could it be that the great
Max Burdett has finally lost?

1252
01:30:24,218 --> 01:30:25,515
No, I didn't.

1253
01:30:27,455 --> 01:30:28,854
I got Lola.

1254
01:30:31,058 --> 01:30:32,719
Congratulations, Stan.

1255
01:30:41,202 --> 01:30:43,261
I'm looking at it right now.

1256
01:30:43,337 --> 01:30:45,965
My plane takes off
in ten minutes.

1257
01:30:46,040 --> 01:30:49,908
Tomorrow morning the bidding
w will start at $30 million,

1258
01:30:49,977 --> 01:30:52,707
and if I were you,
I'd bring cash.

1259
01:31:01,722 --> 01:31:03,656
You win some,
you lose some.

1260
01:31:04,525 --> 01:31:06,618
We still have the sunsets.

1261
01:31:08,796 --> 01:31:09,956
